        <h1>Privacy Policy for VitaL</h1>
        <p class="meta">Last Updated: March 12, 2026</p>

        <p>
            VitaL is a personal supplement tracking app designed to help you
            privately track your supplement routine.
        </p>
        <p>
            VitaL does not use third-party analytics SDKs, advertising SDKs,
            attribution SDKs, or third-party tracking tools, and your data is
            not sold.
        </p>

        <h3>1. Data You Enter in the App</h3>
        <p>
            VitaL stores the data you enter, such as supplement names,
            schedules, intake logs, and consistency reports, so the app can
            function.
        </p>
        <p>
            Your data is stored locally on your device using Apple system
            storage technologies such as SwiftData and UserDefaults. If iCloud
            sync is enabled on your device, your data may also sync through
            Apple’s CloudKit to your private iCloud account so it can stay up to
            date across your personal Apple devices.
        </p>
        <p>
            VitaL does not use its own servers to store your supplement tracking
            data, and your supplement tracking data is not transmitted to the
            developer.
        </p>

        <h3>2. iCloud Sync</h3>
        <p>
            If you use iCloud on your device, VitaL may use Apple’s CloudKit to
            sync your data across your personal Apple devices.
        </p>
        <ul>
            <li>
                Synced data is stored in your private iCloud account, not on
                servers operated by the developer.
            </li>
            <li>
                VitaL does not use its own servers to host this synced data.
            </li>
            <li>
                VitaL does not use your data for analytics, advertising,
                marketing, or profiling.
            </li>
            <li>
                iCloud and CloudKit are services provided by Apple and are
                subject to Apple’s own terms and privacy practices.
            </li>
        </ul>
        <p>
            You can manage your iCloud settings through your Apple ID and iCloud
            settings on your Apple devices.
        </p>

        <h3>3. Crash Reporting</h3>
        <p>VitaL does not include a third-party crash reporting SDK.</p>
        <p>
            If you have chosen to share app diagnostics with developers through
            your Apple device settings, Apple may make anonymized crash
            information available through Apple’s developer tools. This is
            controlled by your device settings and Apple’s own privacy
            practices.
        </p>

        <h3>4. No Third-Party Tracking or Analytics</h3>
        <p>VitaL does not include:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Third-party analytics SDKs</li>
            <li>Advertising SDKs</li>
            <li>Attribution or marketing tracking SDKs</li>
            <li>Third-party crash reporting SDKs</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
            VitaL does not track your in-app activity for advertising,
            profiling, or cross-app tracking purposes.
        </p>

        <h3>5. Subscriptions and Payments</h3>
        <p>
            If you subscribe to VitaL Pro, your purchase is processed by Apple
            through StoreKit.
        </p>
        <p>
            The developer does not collect or store your credit card information
            or billing details. Subscription status is verified on-device using
            StoreKit 2.
        </p>

        <h3>6. Export, Import, and Data Deletion</h3>
        <p>
            VitaL includes tools intended to help you stay in control of your
            data.
        </p>
        <ul>
            <li>Export: You can export your data from the app.</li>
            <li>Import: You can import your data into the app.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
            Data stored locally on your device is removed when you delete the
            app from your device. If iCloud sync is enabled, synced data may
            remain in your private iCloud account until it is removed through
            Apple’s iCloud controls or by the app’s sync behavior.
        </p>

        <h3>7. Your Privacy Rights</h3>
        <p>
            Because VitaL is designed so that your supplement tracking data
            stays on your device and, if enabled, in your private iCloud
            account, the developer generally does not have access to your
            personal tracking data.
        </p>
        <p>
            For that reason, if you request correction of inaccurate data or
            deletion of your data, the developer is generally not able to make
            those changes on your behalf. You can instead update or remove your
            data directly on your device, by using the app, deleting the app, or
            managing your iCloud settings, depending on how your data is stored.
        </p>
        <p>
            If you contact the developer with a privacy question, the developer
            will do their best to explain how VitaL handles data and what
            controls are available to you.
        </p>

        <h3>8. Medical Disclaimer</h3>
        <p>
            VitaL is a personal tracking tool for supplement routines. It does
            not provide medical advice, diagnosis, treatment, or dosage
            recommendations.
        </p>
        <p>
            Any information you log in VitaL is for personal reference only.
            Always consult a qualified healthcare professional before starting,
            stopping, or changing any supplement routine or making health
            decisions.
        </p>

        <h3>9. Children’s Privacy</h3>
        <p>
            VitaL is not directed to children under 13 and is not submitted
            under Apple’s Kids Category.
        </p>

        <h3>10. Changes to This Privacy Policy</h3>
        <p>
            This Privacy Policy may be updated from time to time. If changes are
            made, the “Last Updated” date at the top of this policy will be
            updated. The current version will be made available through the
            app’s website or App Store listing.
        </p>

        <h3>11. Contact</h3>
        <p>If you have questions about this Privacy Policy, please contact:</p>
